arch:property.oc:show_val: Phase X: Site abandonment after major collapse dating to the Byzantine period from the CE 4th to 5th c. New drainage systems are installed including that associated with the newly built west precinct wall.
Blockage in the north doorway of the entrance room (Locus 55)

Locus 56 is the blockage in the doorway of the north wall of the entrance room (Locus 55). The blockage consists of hewn ashlars and one brick, laid roughly in four courses at the bottom of the doorway. Above this blockage is sedimentation and collapse, capped by the lentil of the doorway (Locus 65). Clearly, this blockage was later than the original construction of the doorway, and the similarities of this roughly laid blockage to other alterations in the bath complex justifies its phasing to Stage 4, the period of reconfiguration in the trench.
Unknown north south-by- 0.92 m east west.
